modules.description: Implements command-line interaction with the HiGHS solver, handling argument construction and execution. Operates on `Lp.Problem.t` to generate and solve linear programming problems via external calls. Useful for running optimization tasks with configurable parameters like time limits, logging, and solution tolerances.

This module provides a high-level interface for solving linear programming problems using the HiGHS solver. It includes the `solve` function, which runs the solver with configurable parameters such as time limits, logging, and solution tolerances, and returns the objective value and variable assignments. It operates directly on `Lp.Problem.t` values, enabling end-to-end optimization workflows without requiring manual command-line handling.
